ted by the Federal agency that operates the project, if that agency is not the Department of the Army;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s390b–2/g/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t43/s390b–2/g","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft43%2Fs390b%E2%80%932%2Fg%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"interferes with an authorized purpose of the project;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s390b–2/g/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t43/s390b–2/g","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft43%2Fs390b%E2%80%932%2Fg%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"adversely impacts contractual rights to water or storage at the reservoir;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s390b–2/g/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t43/s390b–2/g","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft43%2Fs390b%E2%80%932%2Fg%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"adversely impacts legal rights to water under State law, as determined by an affected State;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"5","heading":null,"label":"5","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s390b–2/g/5","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t43/s390b–2/g","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft43%2Fs390b%E2%80%932%2Fg%2F5","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"increases costs for any entity other than the entity that submitted the proposal; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"6","heading":null,"label":"6","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s390b–2/g/6","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t43/s390b–2/g","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft43%2Fs390b%E2%80%932%2Fg%2F6","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"if a project is subject to , makes modifications to the project that do not meet the requirements of that section unless the modification is submitted to and authorized by Congress.section 390b(e) of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"h","heading":"Cost share","label":"h Cost share","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s390b–2/h","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t43/s390b–2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft43%2Fs390b%E2%80%932%2Fh","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"In general","label":"1 In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s390b–2/h/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t43/s390b–2/h","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft43%2Fs390b%E2%80%932%2Fh%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Except as provided in paragraph (2), 100 percent of the cost of developing, reviewing, and implementing a proposal submitted under subsection (a) shall be provided by an entity other than the Federal Government.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"Planning assistance to states","label":"2 Planning assistance to states","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s390b–2/h/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t43/s390b–2/h","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft43%2Fs390b%E2%80%932%2Fh%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"In the case of a proposal from an entity authorized to receive assistance under , the Secretary may use funds available under that section to pay 50 percent of the cost of a review of a proposal submitted under subsection (a).section 1962d–16 of title 42","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":"Operation and maintenance costs","label":"3 Operation and maintenance costs","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s390b–2/h/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t43/s390b–2/h","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft43%2Fs390b%E2%80%932%2Fh%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":"In general","label":"A In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s390b–2/h/3/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t43/s390b–2/h/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft43%2Fs390b%E2%80%932%2Fh%2F3%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Except as provided in subparagraphs (B) and (C), the operation and maintenance costs for the non-Federal sponsor of a proposal submitted under subsection (a) shall be 100 percent of the separable operation and maintenance costs associated with the costs of implementing the proposal.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":"Certain water supply storage projects","label":"B Certain water supply storage projects","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s390b–2/h/3/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t43/s390b–2/h/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft43%2Fs390b%E2%80%932%2Fh%2F3%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"For a proposal submitted under subsection (a) for constructing additional water supply storage at a reservoir for use under a water supply storage agreement, in addition to the costs under subparagraph (A), the non-Federal costs shall include the proportional share of any joint-use costs for operation, maintenance, repair, replacement, or rehabilitation of the reservoir project determined in accordance with .section 390b of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":"Voluntary contributions","label":"C Voluntary contributions","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s390b–2/h/3/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t43/s390b–2/h/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft43%2Fs390b%E2%80%932%2Fh%2F3%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"An entity other than an entity described in subparagraph (A) may voluntarily contribute to the costs of implementing a proposal submitted under subsection (a).","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"i","heading":"Contributed funds","label":"i Contributed funds","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s390b–2/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t43/s390b–2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft43%2Fs390b%E2%80%932%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"Contributed funds for corps projects","label":"1 Contributed funds for corps projects","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s390b–2/i/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t43/s390b–2/i","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft43%2Fs390b%E2%80%932%2Fi%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Secretary may may receive and expend funds contributed by a non-Federal interest for the review and approval of a proposal submitted under subsection (a).","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"Contributed funds for other Federal reservoir projects","label":"2 Contributed funds for other Federal reservoir projects","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s390b–2/i/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t43/s390b–2/i","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft43%2Fs390b%E2%80%932%2Fi%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":"In general","label":"A In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s390b–2/i/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t43/s390b–2/i/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft43%2Fs390b%E2%80%932%2Fi%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Secretary is authorized to receive and expend funds from a non-Federal interest or a Federal agency that owns a Federal reservoir project described in subparagraph (B) to formulate, review, or revise operational documents pursuant to a proposal submitted in accordance with subsection (a) for such a Federal reservoir project.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":"Federal reservoir projects described","label":"B Federal reservoir projects described","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s390b–2/i/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t43/s390b–2/i/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft43%2Fs390b%E2%80%932%2Fi%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"A Federal reservoir project referred to in subparagraph (A) is a reservoir for which the Secretary is authorized to prescribe regulations for the use of storage allocated for flood control or navigation pursuant to .section 709 of title 33","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"j","heading":"Assistance","label":"j Assistance","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s390b–2/j","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t43/s390b–2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft43%2Fs390b%E2%80%932%2Fj","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"On request by a non-Federal interest, the Secretary may provide technical assistance in the development or implementation of a proposal under subsection (a), including assistance in obtaining necessary permits for construction, if the non-Federal interest contracts with the Secretary to pay all costs of providing the technical assistance.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"k","heading":"Exclusion","label":"k Exclusion","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s390b–2/k","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t43/s390b–2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft43%2Fs390b%E2%80%932%2Fk","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s390b–2/k/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t43/s390b–2/k","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft43%2Fs390b%E2%80%932%2Fk%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the Upper Missouri River;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s390b–2/k/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t43/s390b–2/k","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft43%2Fs390b%E2%80%932%2Fk%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the Apalachicola-Chattahoochee-Flint river system;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s390b–2/k/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t43/s390b–2/k","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft43%2Fs390b%E2%80%932%2Fk%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the Alabama-Coosa-Tallapoosa river system; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s390b–2/k/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t43/s390b–2/k","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft43%2Fs390b%E2%80%932%2Fk%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the Stones River.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"l","heading":"Effect of section","label":"l Effect of section","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s390b–2/l","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t43/s390b–2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft43%2Fs390b%E2%80%932%2Fl","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Nothing in this section affects or modifies any authority of the Secretary to review or modify reservoirs.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}
